      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OHOKA DREAM (8) has the hoof on the till after finishing second at this circuit and distance in both starts since a spell, missing by just a nose last week. Draws on the back row this time but should enjoy a nice trail and the sprint lane is in play so can peak and win. Hard to knock the recent consistency of MAHINDI NZ (4) who added to a string of wins and placings when second and just a nose from the winner here last week. Scored a hat-trick of Redcliffe wins last month. Leading hope. INTERPRETATION (7) draws wide but brings consistent form from Victoria where she recorded back-to-back placings before working from the back row for fourth last week at Cranbourne. Could measure up with even luck. ALTA SENSATION NZ (1) will be fitter for recent racing and the ace draw may spark big improvement.",
